Bruce-

Here is something I did in the past. Put a hose on the bleed valve and
run it into a jar with brake fluid so the tip of the hose is submerged. As
you fill the master cylinder and pump the brakes all of the air will go
through the hose but not back in. It will take a little more brake fluid
than normal because you will probably pump more than you need.

Good luck,
Steven

