Bruce:

I have used the MityVac system to bleed the brakes many times on my pick up
trucks. It works pretty good. I provides a vacuum to pull the fluid and air
out of the brake cylinders. Make sure that you keep the master cylinder
filled with brake fluid or you can bleed it dry. Start at the wheel farthest
away (usually passenger side rear) from the master cylinder and work your way
to the closest (usually driver rear, passenger front and finally driver
front). It beats having your wife mad at you for having to keep pumping the
brake. ;-)

Mick
HotRod 53 F-100
65 Chev C-10

