How does this work properly with disc brakes? They don't have return
springs. As far as I know, it's the release of pressure only that causes the
pads to release the pressure. This is why when you replace the pads you have
to push the cylinder back in the caliper. If there is something I'm
misinformed about please let me know.

-sheepdog

