It works the same. The square cut oring acts as a return spring. It will
retract the piston just enough so the pad will not drag. There are other
conditions that cause the pad to drag anyway. And with volume the piston
displaces it will push plenty of fluid back to avoid air being drawn in.
Beware that if the bleed screw is open too much, it will not work at all.

